The paper proposes a cooperative framework for coordinating semi-autonomous vehicles in complex traffic situations, which involves the use of advanced driver assistance systems (ADAS) and supervised coordination schemes. This suggests a focus on robotics (cs.RO) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) in the development of the algorithm. The paper also emphasizes the need for safe and efficient coordination, which involves system-level control and optimization (cs.SY), as well as machine learning techniques for supervised learning (cs.LG) and computer vision for perception and decision-making (cs.CV).
